Files:
- plugins/grafana/src/index.ts (add configSchema, change urlPatterns to [])
- plugins/grafana/package.json (add configSchema to opentabs field, change urlPatterns to [], remove homepage)

Context:
The plugin SDK supports configSchema with url-type settings. When a plugin declares a required url-type field and sets urlPatterns to [], the platform derives Chrome match patterns and homepage from the configured URL at runtime. This enables plugins to work with self-hosted instances without hardcoded URL patterns.

The e2e-test plugin already implements this pattern. Use it as a reference.

Current code in plugins/grafana/src/index.ts:
```typescript
class GrafanaPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'grafana';
  readonly description =
    'OpenTabs plugin for Grafana — manage dashboards, folders, data sources, alerts, annotations, teams, and more.';
  override readonly displayName = 'Grafana';
  readonly urlPatterns = ['*://*.grafana.net/*'];
  override readonly homepage = 'https://grafana.com';
```

Change to:
```typescript
import type { ConfigSchema } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';

class GrafanaPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'grafana';
  readonly description =
    'OpenTabs plugin for Grafana — manage dashboards, folders, data sources, alerts, annotations, teams, and more.';
  override readonly displayName = 'Grafana';
  readonly urlPatterns: string[] = [];
  override readonly configSchema: ConfigSchema = {
    instanceUrl: {
      type: 'url',
      label: 'Grafana URL',
      description: 'The URL of your Grafana instance (e.g., https://myorg.grafana.net or https://grafana.internal)',
      required: true,
      placeholder: 'https://myorg.grafana.net',
    },
  };
```

Remove the `override readonly homepage = 'https://grafana.com';` line — homepage is derived from the configured URL.

Current package.json opentabs field:
```json
"opentabs": {
  "displayName": "Grafana",
  "description": "OpenTabs plugin for Grafana",
  "urlPatterns": [
    "*://*.grafana.net/*"
  ],
  "homepage": "https://grafana.com"
}
```

Change to:
```json
"opentabs": {
  "displayName": "Grafana",
  "description": "OpenTabs plugin for Grafana",
  "urlPatterns": [],
  "configSchema": {
    "instanceUrl": {
      "type": "url",
      "label": "Grafana URL",
      "description": "The URL of your Grafana instance (e.g., https://myorg.grafana.net or https://grafana.internal)",
      "required": true,
      "placeholder": "https://myorg.grafana.net"
    }
  }
}
```

Constraints:
- Do NOT modify any tool files or grafana-api.ts — they already use relative URLs (`/api/...`) via fetchJSON, which work with any base URL.
- The `ConfigSchema` type import already exists in the SDK: `import type { ConfigSchema } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';`
- Use `as const` for the type field value if needed for type inference, like the e2e-test plugin does: `type: 'url' as const`
